<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="41" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,361,593]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName authority="Guillen and Davis" authorityName="Guillen and Davis" box="[151,566,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Marmara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gulosa">
<emphasis box="[151,344,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Marmara gulosa</emphasis>
Guillén and Davis
</taxonomicName>
, the citrus peelminer, has been reported as a pest of avocado in California (
<bibRefCitation author="Waite" box="[158,730,396,420]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refString="Waite, G. K. &amp; Barrera, M. (2002) Insect and mite pests, pp. 339 - 361. In: Whiley, A. W., Schaffer, B. and Wolstenholme, B. N. (eds.), The avocado: botany, production and uses. CAB International." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Waite and Barrera 
<number box="[374,433,396,420]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" value="2002.0">2002</number>
; as 
<taxonomicName authority="Clemens" authorityName="Clemens" box="[477,730,396,420]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Marmara" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salictella">
<emphasis box="[477,619,396,420]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">M. salictella</emphasis>
Clemens
</taxonomicName>
</bibRefCitation>
). Larvae cause damage by mining the surface of fruit, causing significant scarring, and they may also mine shoots and leaves (
<bibRefCitation author="Guillen" box="[901,1127,431,455]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refString="Guillen, M., Davis, D. R. &amp; Heraty, J. M. (2001) Systematics and biology of a new, polyphagous species of Marmara (Lepidoptera: Gracillariidae) infesting grapefruit in the southwestern United States. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 103, 636 - 654." type="journal article" year="2001">
Guillén 
<emphasis box="[998,1057,431,455]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1068,1127,431,455]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Waite" box="[1142,1425,431,455]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refString="Waite, G. K. &amp; Barrera, M. (2002) Insect and mite pests, pp. 339 - 361. In: Whiley, A. W., Schaffer, B. and Wolstenholme, B. N. (eds.), The avocado: botany, production and uses. CAB International." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Waite and Barrera 
<number box="[1364,1425,431,455]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Busck" authorityName="Busck" box="[151,457,465,489]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Caloptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perseae">
<emphasis box="[151,359,465,489]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Caloptilia perseae</emphasis>
(Busck)
</taxonomicName>
is considered a pest of avocado in 
<collectingCountry box="[859,947,465,489]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">México</collectingCountry>
, where larvae mine leaves but rarely cause significant damage (
<bibRefCitation author="Wysoki" box="[379,599,500,524]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refString="Wysoki, M., van den Berg, M. A., Ish-Am, G., Gazit, S., Pena, J. E. &amp; Waite, G. K. (2002) Pests and pollinators of avocado, pp. 223 - 294. In: Pena, J. E., Sharp, L. J. and Mysoki, M. (eds.), Tropical fruit pests and pollinators, biology, economic importance, natural enemies and control. CAB International." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Wysoki 
<emphasis box="[474,531,500,524]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[538,599,500,524]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Davis" box="[618,907,500,525]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" refString="Davis, D. R. &amp; Wagner, D. L. (2011) Biology and systematics of the New World Phyllocnistis Zeller leafminers of the avocado genus Persea (Lepidoptera, Gracillariidae). ZooKeys, 97, 39 - 73." type="journal article" year="2011">
Davis and Wagner (
<number box="[842,900,500,524]" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described several new species of 
<taxonomicName box="[1291,1436,500,524]" class="Insecta" family="Gracillariidae" genus="Phyllocnistis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1291,1436,500,524]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">Phyllocnistis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Central 
<collectingCountry box="[305,401,535,559]" name="United States of America" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">America</collectingCountry>
and the southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[651,700,535,559]" name="United States of America" pageId="10" pageNumber="41">U.S.</collectingCountry>
that mine leaves of avocado; none of these species are recorded from California.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
